Washington.name: Crumbs & Whiskers | Kitten & Cat Cafe.
Washington.address: 3109 M St NW, Washington, DC 20007, USA

text.text: Really fantastic place that lets you hang out with adoptable cats in an awesome atmosphere! It‚Äôs especially nice for people like me who cannot adopt another animal myself but loves animal experiences and supporting rescue. The facility was clean, decorated beautifully, staff were really friendly and shared background stories on the cats and the kitty cats are all clearly well cared for. Visited Washington DC from Milwaukee, WI and I‚Äôm so glad we added this to our travel itinerary. The free Polaroid snapshot is such a nice touch and so unique (I‚Äôve been to 10 cat cafes and this is the only one I‚Äôve seen do this). I wish caffeine free tea options were available and would have preferred an hour long session for the price we paid but it‚Äôs for a fantastic cause so - 5/5 stars!

The sweetest cats I've ever encountered at any cat cafe. They were all happy and chillin. Some would approach you and others were so relaxed and happy they didn't mind at all when you approached them. A sweet cat in particular climbed right into my lap ‚ù§Ô∏èüòÅ we got a nice polaroid taken of me and my friend and now have that as a keepsake. From what I overheard, it sounds like all of the cats get adopted pretty quick. It feels good to support a place like this that does a lot of good things for cats and also is quite fun for me too!

Went for some kitty cuddle time and was not disappointed. The staff was friendly and kept a sharp eye on the cats. The cats were playful and energetic. We didn't get any food or drinks but they did have a menu. No shoes in the car hangout space so be sure to wear socks when you go. Also be patient, the cats operate on their own schedule.

Washington.name: Meow Maison
Washington.address: 1336 Wisconsin Ave NW, Washington, DC 20007, USA

text.text:
The second cat cafe in my tour of DC area ones. I definitely liked the vibe. It's not inexpensive but given that they only allow four people in at a time and their pricey location, it's understandable.

The cats are fun, and the staff are friendly. You do have to take off your shoes so be ready for that. Even the owner abides by that rule.

The staff will introduce you to the cats but you'll forget in a minute and they're happy to answer your questions about the cats time and again.

This is definitely a place to have fun with a bunch of furry friends.

I‚Äôve been to Meow Maison multiple times to hang out with the kitties, and it has been a wonderful experience every time. The cats are very well taken care of, and the atmosphere is super cozy! The staff are also very friendly and helpful if you have any questions regarding adoption.

I initially came into this cafe with my best friend just to chill with some cats, but ended up adopting two little ones! Everyone was super supportive and helpful with the process. The second adoption was very last second (during the adoption of the first), yet the people who were working that day, and the volunteer (Jessie), who helped me were INCREDIBLY accommodating. Not only that, they let me borrow a carrier because I came with just the one. The girl who helped me during the drop off of the carrier later is super appreciated as well.

Every step of the way, Meow Maison was 10/10

cafes.name: NEKO Cat Cafe Seattle
cafes.address: 519 E Pine St, Seattle, WA 98122, USA

text.text: This was such a great experience! we were in Seattle traveling for the week and missing our cats at home, so we decided to pop in for a visit! $25 for a 45 minute session with the cutest, sweetest, cats in Seattle! I definitely recommend coming here as the fee goes to a good cause, and you get a great experience out of it. It‚Äôs very clear that these cats are loved and well taken care of! I also recommend the Fez Mint Tea! It was delicious on that cold Seattle night. :)

I booked an appointment in advance to visit the Neko kitties. The staff was friendly and it was nice to have drinks and snacks available. The visit was 45 minutes long and time was shared with 8-10 cats and a few other people who had booked. I loved the cats even if many of them were ready for naps during our visit. Some of the cats are residents while others are available for adoption. Staff wipe down the space between visits. Well run cafe!  I'd love to go back if I'm ever back in Seattle!

Great experience. I had visited once before in passing for a beverage and a peek at the kitties, but I'm happy to have been able to book a visit with the kitties this time around. It was definitely worth it! Be sure to check out the sweet pickles collar bow ties if you're looking to spice up your own kitty's wardrobe.

OMG what pretty kitty's! Reasonably priced and you can choose 30 minutes or 50 minutes to play with these beautiful creatures. There were only 2 cats up for adoption I'm sure they'll have more soon. Not much of a food selection just cookies mainly but would definitely recommend going here!

I went to Cat-o-latern-pumpkin carving session this year and it was an amazing experience! The cafe is very clean, and there‚Äôs a variety of drinks to choose from (coffee, tea,  juice and alcoholic beverages). The cafe also has a great merchandise section and everything is so cute (I got some gifts for myself and for my cat). The cat lounge itself has very cat-friendly layout, and you can tell it‚Äôs a very tidy and comfortable environment for those cats. The kitties are all very relaxed, and a few of them very playful and energetic. All staff at this place are super friendly and patient, and the cats show great affection for their human coworkers. I would recommend this place to all cat lovers, and I would definitely come back for another visit.

Must visit when in Seattle!
Enjoy a cup of coffee while cudding with cats.

The coffee is the best ive had in the USA.
Unfortunately only macaroons available for sweet snacks (im not a macaroon fan)
The service is phenomenal. From the moment we stepped in it was all smiles and the lady explained the process in detail.

Bookings are recommended if you want to interact with the cats. Half sessions or full sessions available. $10-$19. (No kids under 6 allowed in with the cats)
We are traveling with our 2year old and could not touch the cats - and we still had an amazing experience.

Amazing little shop area too with everything cat. From shirts, card games, hair accessories, crystals and of-course, toys for cats.

Fun little experience! Pleasant staff, clean atmosphere, aloof cats. I made a mistake when booking tickets. I called them, and the nice young woman who answered was able to quickly fix my mistake. The experience was lovely and sweet. I'd recommend this for neurodivergent people who don't want to be overstimulated.

My fianc√© and I went for a day trip from Canada to the US and he brought me to the Neko Cat Cafe! We were very excited for the experience. When arriving, I could see how much they care for the cats; it almost felt like the cats ran the cafe and the employees were just there to feed them :D I was very pleased with how clean the environment was and how cat friendly everything was. They also serve alcohol and nonalcoholic beverages which was a bonus!

Simon will forever be in my heart!
I love all the kitties! Luna, Prairie, Tilly, and Freya have all sat in my lap! The cats are all really chill, and super funny.

cafes.name: Pawsific NorthWest Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 3415 Pacific Ave SE F-1, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

text.text: Support local businesses and artists by coming here! I can't say enough good about this place! I adopted my 2 kittens from here and they're so sweet and well socialized. The drinks are always delicious with a huge array of flavors, and the staff os super friendly. I love bringing my kids here and seeing all of the new cats and enjoying the clean, calming environment. They also sell and showcase different mediums of art from local artists! 11/10 my fave spot.

I had such a wonderful experience! I highly recommend you go, and it's only $10 on Wednesdays! Such a great deal for an unforgettable experience. The music is calm, the room is quiet and clean, and the staff is great too. The food and drink options are amazing too!

The cats are also really happy to be there and are very relaxed and warm. I could stay there all day if I could! :)

Note: I read the negative reviews, and as a Veterinary assistant, I can easily state that the staff at the cafe absolutely are doing everything correctly when it comes to animal care including diet, handling of animals, cleanliness, and more.

It is very obvious that they are doing everything right.

Adorable cats! We got there rather late in the evening and enjoyed some espresso while chilling with some sleepy playful kits, love the work this cafe is doing! We got a weekday special, $10 for entry to the cat room and some espresso free of charge! The staff is wonderful and really cares about the cats ‚ô•Ô∏è definitely a neat place to check out if you‚Äôve been curious about cat cafes!

cafes.name: Kitty Cantina
cafes.address: 6704 N Nevada St #1, Spokane, WA 99208, USA

text.text:
I drove by the Kitty Cantina and decided to stop in on a whim. I‚Äôm so glad I did! The staff are so welcoming. The environment is really positive and upbeat and all the cats are super sweet and fun.

I ordered an iced Matcha latte with oat milk, and made a walk-in appointment to spend time with the cats. They had a half hour and an hour option. a drink and a half hour cost about $13- well worth it in my opinion and I heard a couple other people mentioned it was the best money they spent all week!

Some cats snoozed other cats liked to play and they were plenty of kitties to go around! in my session, there were four other people in the room and there were about 15 cats.

Highly recommend a visit if you‚Äôre looking for some tasty food and time with some sweet cats!

The food here is so good! Very creative names of the food and it tastes just amazing. My son and I love to come here for a bagel or to get some lunch, it's always a treat. Drinks are good too and you can't beat being able to watch some adorable kittens run around while you enjoy your fare.

Out of all the cat cafes i‚Äôve been to this is one of the only ones that actually has good coffee and good food. The coffee is better than some local shops around town! The staff is very nice and well knowledgeable, and of course the kitties are insanely cute. everything is very reasonably priced too!

cafes.name: Ziggy's Cat Lounge
cafes.address: 3627 Wheaton Wy Suite F, Bremerton, WA 98310, USA

text.text: I love going to Ziggy‚Äôs! It‚Äôs such an awesome way to socialize with kitties and then being able to adopt them! You can tell the kitties are well taken care of and happy. I love going and have a blast every time! The coffee is super good too!

Such a lovely place doing amazing work for kitties looking for forever homes! All of the cats here were sooo friendly, and it was such a good mix of ages and personalities. I've been to other cat lounges/cafes in the area and was a bit disappointed, but this place offered exactly the experience you hope for from a cat lounge! Caution: it will be very, very hard not to leave with one (or more!)

Surprised my partner with a visit here on his birthday and we both loved it!! The kittens are so sweet, lots of toys to play with them and I love that there‚Äôs a few spaces for them to get away when they get overwhelmed with all the attention. I didn‚Äôt try anything from the cafe but I love that you can take drinks into the cat room.
I always check the bad reviews just for funsies and I love to see Shannon standing on business with the people that love to be difficult! I only talked to her very briefly but she seems sweet, the kitties are well taken care of and the rules are very clear so that everyone can enjoy the lounge and keep the kitties safe and happy. Just make sure you book ahead of time since it fills up quickly and read the rules you‚Äôre agreeing, it‚Äôs not that hard people!!
